Honestly, the better solution using Java would be to perform the if statement logic in its own method that returns UserParameter and then add the UserParameter as an optional argument to your existing method so that you&#39;re always only returning one object.
```
public UserParameter getUserParameter(GetChannelAccountReq request) {
